<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,341,870]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,341,366]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body dark castaneous nearly black, mostly with metallic colour reflections. Head with dense compound eye pilosity; mandible with four or five distal teeth in females, and five distal teeth in males; clypeal carina complete and arched in lateral profile; antennal scrobe usuallycarinate. Pronotum with transverse carina, absent in few species. Notaulus complete; anterior half of parapsidal signum continuous. Metapectal-propodeal disc with metapostnotal carina incomplete, and not fused with posterior carina; propodeal declivity sculptured. Mesopleuron with all foveae well defined. Female genitalia with 2vf (second valvifer) very swollen apically. Male genitalia with basiparamere mostly dorsal; cuspis bifid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,341,870]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,593,618]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
Some characters were observed for the first time in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1905" box="[916,1034,594,617]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[916,1034,594,617]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Anisepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as the claw-shaped mandible (
<figureCitation box="[159,251,629,654]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1942,1964]" captionTargetBox="[224,1359,232,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[182,1404,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 5. Anisepyris: aeneus species-group. A–B. Head in dorsal profile. A. A. tlaloc Evans, 1966; B. A. wolcotti Evans, 1959; C–H. Female mandible in frontal profile; I–J. Male mandible in frontal profile; K–R. Mesosoma in dorsal profile; S. Mesopleuron in frontalprofile." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242273/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
); the serrate antenna (
<figureCitation box="[520,629,629,654]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="82.[151,250,1889,1911]" captionTargetBox="[242,1342,231,1827]" captionTargetId="figure@82.[201,1386,193,1868]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURE 14. Anisepyris: columbianus species-group.A–I.Head in dorsal profile. A. A.occidentalis (Ashmead, 1893) (♀); B. A. occidentalis (Ashmead, 1893) (♂); C. A. penai Evans, 1966; D. A. sculptilis Evans, 1966; E. A. similis Santos &amp; Azevedo, 2000; F. A. subviolaceus Kieffer, 1910; G. A. westwoodi (Cameron, 1888); H. A. williamsi Evans, 1959 (♀); I. A. williamsi Evans, 1959 (♂); J. Male manbible in frontal profile; K–N. Female manbible in frontal profile; O. Male antenna in lateral profile." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242291/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 14O</figureCitation>
); the antenna with second and third flagellomeres with distal spine projection (
<figureCitation box="[280,386,665,690]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="100.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[222,1375,235,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[179,1421,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 15. Anisepyris: columbianus species-group. A–B. Male antenna in dorsal profile; C. Head in lateral profile; D–J. Mesosoma in dorsal profile; K–M. Mesopleuron in frontal profile." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242293/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
); the very long and slender clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[803,882,665,690]" captionStart="FIGURE6" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1942,1964]" captionTargetBox="[224,1359,232,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[182,1404,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE6. Anisepyris: aeneus species-group.A–C.Mesopleuron in frontalprofile; amazonicus species-group.Head in dorsal profile.D. A. aegnori sp. nov.; E. A. aerini sp. nov.; F.A.aghani sp. nov.; G. A.amandili sp. nov.; H. A.amariei sp. nov.; I. A. amrodi sp. nov.; J. A.bregolasi sp. nov.; K.A.broddai sp. nov.; L.A. beori sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242275/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<date box="[856,882,665,690]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">6I</date>
</figureCitation>
); the clypeal carina fused and indistinct from the clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[253,342,701,726]" captionStart="FIGURE6" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1942,1964]" captionTargetBox="[224,1359,232,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[182,1404,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE6. Anisepyris: aeneus species-group.A–C.Mesopleuron in frontalprofile; amazonicus species-group.Head in dorsal profile.D. A. aegnori sp. nov.; E. A. aerini sp. nov.; F.A.aghani sp. nov.; G. A.amandili sp. nov.; H. A.amariei sp. nov.; I. A. amrodi sp. nov.; J. A.bregolasi sp. nov.; K.A.broddai sp. nov.; L.A. beori sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242275/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
) or the carina very swollen (
<figureCitation box="[668,756,701,726]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[224,1359,234,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[182,1404,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 3. Anisepyris: aeneus species-group. Head in dorsal profile. A. A. amrasis sp. nov.; B. A. aradunakhori sp. nov.; C. A. arpharazoni sp. nov.; D. A. barahiris sp. nov.; E. A. barani sp. nov.; F. A.belegundi sp. nov.; G. A. belemiri sp. nov.; H. A. beregi sp. nov.; I. A. bereni sp. nov.; J. A.borladi sp. nov.; K. A.boromiri sp. nov.; L. A.borthandis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242269/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); the transverse pronotal carina with a series of foveae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="100.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[222,1375,235,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[179,1421,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 15. Anisepyris: columbianus species-group. A–B. Male antenna in dorsal profile; C. Head in lateral profile; D–J. Mesosoma in dorsal profile; K–M. Mesopleuron in frontal profile." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242293/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
); the pronotal disc with a median longitudinal line (
<figureCitation box="[800,901,737,762]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="100.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[222,1375,235,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[179,1421,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 15. Anisepyris: columbianus species-group. A–B. Male antenna in dorsal profile; C. Head in lateral profile; D–J. Mesosoma in dorsal profile; K–M. Mesopleuron in frontal profile." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242293/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 15F</figureCitation>
); the posterior pronotal sulcus with a series of foveae (
<figureCitation box="[244,347,773,798]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="100.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[222,1375,235,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[179,1421,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 15. Anisepyris: columbianus species-group. A–B. Male antenna in dorsal profile; C. Head in lateral profile; D–J. Mesosoma in dorsal profile; K–M. Mesopleuron in frontal profile." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242293/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
); the posterior mesoscutellar sulcus present (
<figureCitation box="[867,974,773,798]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="100.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[222,1375,235,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[179,1421,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 15. Anisepyris: columbianus species-group. A–B. Male antenna in dorsal profile; C. Head in lateral profile; D–J. Mesosoma in dorsal profile; K–M. Mesopleuron in frontal profile." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242293/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 15D</figureCitation>
); the first pair metapostnotal carina and metapostnotal-propodeal suture convergent or fused (
<figureCitation box="[761,858,809,834]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="100.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[222,1375,235,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[179,1421,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 15. Anisepyris: columbianus species-group. A–B. Male antenna in dorsal profile; C. Head in lateral profile; D–J. Mesosoma in dorsal profile; K–M. Mesopleuron in frontal profile." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242293/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 15J</figureCitation>
); and all characteristics related to female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,845,870]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="241.[151,250,1363,1385]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,501,1323]" captionTargetId="figure@241.[226,1360,482,1341]" captionTargetPageId="241" captionText="FIGURE 30. Structures of the female genitalia of Anisepyris. First valvulae (1vl); second valvulae (2vl); third valvulae (3vl); first valvifers (1vlf); second valvifers (2vlf); first rami valvularum (1rvlf); second rami valvularum (2rvlf); furcula (fu); intervalvifer articulation (IA); ninth abdominal tergum (T9)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242323/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
